SENATE BILL No. 69
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
pensions.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 36-8-8-16, AS AMENDED BY P.L.28-2008,
2 SECTION 4, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 16. (a) Benefits paid under this section are subject
4 to section 2.5 of this chapter.
5 (b) The heirs or estate of a fund member is entitled to receive at
6 least twelve thousand dollars ($12,000) fifteen thousand dollars
7 ($15,000) upon the fund member's death, adjusted annually by the
8 percentage increase, if any, in the consumer price index as
9 calculated under section 15 of this chapter.
10 (c) The board shall annually publish the total benefit payable
11 under this section on the board's website.
12 SECTION 2. IC 36-8-8.5-8 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
13 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 8. As used in this
14 chapter, "DROP retirement date" means the future retirement date
15 selected by a member at the time the member makes a DROP election
16 or extension.
17 SECTION 3. IC 36-8-8.5-10.5, AS ADDED BY P.L.129-2024,
